# tone(9, 440, 300)'s initial HIGH-frequency state can't actually be observed
# here: ASSERT PIN only checks state at loop()-call boundaries (once per full
# ~500ms loop() call, since loop() itself is delay(500) + a print), and the
# 300ms tone duration has already elapsed and cleared the pin back to 0 by
# the time the very first boundary check is possible. Only the post-clear
# state is meaningfully assertable -- which is also the actual regression
# this sketch exists for (the duration thread correctly clearing the pin).
0.5, ASSERT, PIN, 9, 0
